Usage: setSelectedRouteBlk [-help] <llx> <lly> <urx> <ury> <name> <layers>
                           [<attr>] [<spacing>]

-help              # Prints out the command usage
<llx>              # lower left x coordinate of the bounding box
                   # (float, required)
<lly>              # lower left y coordinate of the bounding box
                   # (float, required)
<urx>              # upper right x coordinate of the bounding box
                   # (float, required)
<ury>              # upper right y coordinate of the bounding box
                   # (float, required)
<name>             # name of the routing blockage (string, required)
<layers>           # the layer(s) and/or via(s) (string, required)
<attr>             # attribute of the routing blockage,
                   # {Undefined|Fills|Slots|Partial Pushdown
                   # EXCEPTPGNET|PGNETONLY|ALLNET} (string, optional)
<spacing>          # minimum spacing between layers within the routing blockage
                   # or effective width of the routing blockage {-spacing |
                   # -designRuleWidth} (string, optional)